docs.abstract: Imran Khan, the presumptive prime minister, has sought to temper his past anti-American speech. But his election could signal more tensions in an already strained relationship.
docs.snippet: Imran Khan, the presumptive prime minister, has sought to temper his past anti-American speech. But his election could signal more tensions in an already strained relationship.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The rise of Imran Khan, a former cricket star who is Pakistan’s likely next leader, could complicate new talks between American diplomats and the Taliban about ending the war in Afghanistan, officials said, fraying an already strained relationship between the nuclear-armed Islamic nation and the Trump administration.

headline.main: Pakistan’s Likely New Leader Could Complicate Afghan Peace Talks
headline.print_headline: Rise of Critic in Pakistan Could Strain U.S. Efforts

docs.abstract: The lawyer, Michael Avenatti, has insisted that the case against the president and his lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, is not political.
docs.snippet: The lawyer, Michael Avenatti, has insisted that the case against the president and his lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, is not political.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Michael Avenatti, the lawyer for Stephanie Clifford, the pornographic film actress who says she had a sexual encounter with President Trump, has sought help for his legal battle against Mr. Trump from leading Democratic operatives.

headline.main: Stormy Daniels’s Lawyer Sought Help From Democrats in Fight With Trump
headline.print_headline: Lawyer for Porn Actress Sought Help From Top Democratic Donors

docs.abstract: In his first public remarks on the matter, President Trump told reporters that he knew nothing about the $130,000 paid to Stormy Daniels, remarks that could complicate his legal battle against her.
docs.snippet: In his first public remarks on the matter, President Trump told reporters that he knew nothing about the $130,000 paid to Stormy Daniels, remarks that could complicate his legal battle against her.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump denied on Thursday knowing of a $130,000 payment his lawyer made to a pornographic film actress who claims to have had a sexual encounter with him, an assertion that threatened to complicate his legal battle against her.

headline.main: Trump Denies Knowing of Any Hush Money Paid to Porn Actress
headline.print_headline: Trump Denies Knowledge Of Payment To Porn Star

docs.abstract: In a report, Education Department staff members found that the former accreditor of Corinthian Colleges and ITT Tech had violated dozens of federal standards.
docs.snippet: In a report, Education Department staff members found that the former accreditor of Corinthian Colleges and ITT Tech had violated dozens of federal standards.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos disregarded a scathing review by her own staff this spring when she reinstated the watchdog body that had accredited two scandal-scarred for-profit universities whose bankruptcies left tens of thousands of students with worthless degrees and mountains of debt, a new report has revealed.

headline.main: Betsy DeVos Reinstated College Accreditor Over Staff Objections
headline.print_headline: DeVos Overruled Staff to Reinstate College Accreditor

docs.abstract: The president’s racially charged comments threaten an emerging agreement to project some undocumented immigrants, which risks bringing a government shutdown.
docs.snippet: The president’s racially charged comments threaten an emerging agreement to project some undocumented immigrants, which risks bringing a government shutdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was just after President Trump had finished railing in the Oval Office against African immigrants he said came from “shithole countries” when a senior Republican senator, Lindsey Graham of South Carolina, who was there to negotiate a deal on immigration, spoke up.

headline.main: A Senior Republican Senator Admonishes Trump: ‘America Is an Idea, Not a Race’
headline.print_headline: G.O.P. Senator Scolded Trump After Vile Talk

docs.abstract: The House gave final approval to a measure that would fund the federal government for another three weeks, ending a three-day old government shutdown.
docs.snippet: The House gave final approval to a measure that would fund the federal government for another three weeks, ending a three-day old government shutdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: • The House passed a short-term spending bill to reopen the government. Next, President Trump must sign it to end the shutdown.

headline.main: Stopgap Bill to End Government Shutdown Passes Congress

docs.abstract: The White House aide who resigned in a domestic abuse scandal that engulfed the White House was known for his ambition at Harvard and on Capitol Hill.
docs.snippet: The White House aide who resigned in a domestic abuse scandal that engulfed the White House was known for his ambition at Harvard and on Capitol Hill.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — People who crossed paths with Rob Porter in Harvard classrooms or the hallways of Capitol Hill describe him in glowing terms: He was articulate enough to be secretary of state. Intelligent enough to be a Supreme Court justice. Driven enough to be president.

headline.main: Rob Porter’s Charisma and Ambition Disguised Flare-ups of Anger
headline.print_headline: Aide’s Clean-Cut Image Belied His Hot Temper, Former Colleagues Say

docs.abstract: The young people, as they seized the nation’s attention, vowed that their grief about school shootings and their frustration with adults’ inaction would power a new generation of activism.
docs.snippet: The young people, as they seized the nation’s attention, vowed that their grief about school shootings and their frustration with adults’ inaction would power a new generation of activism.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Standing before vast crowds from Washington to Los Angeles to Parkland, Fla., the speakers — nearly all of them students, some still in elementary school — delivered an anguished and defiant message: They are “done hiding” from gun violence, and will “stop at nothing” to get politicians to finally prevent it.

headline.main: Students Lead Huge Rallies for Gun Control Across the U.S.
headline.print_headline: With Passion and Fury, Students March on Guns

docs.abstract: Mr. Carson has been whipsawed by a job he has found puzzling, with his goals undermined by his indecisiveness, his staffing mistakes and a president indifferent to his department’s mission.
docs.snippet: Mr. Carson has been whipsawed by a job he has found puzzling, with his goals undermined by his indecisiveness, his staffing mistakes and a president indifferent to his department’s mission.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Before Ben Carson accepted President Trump’s offer to become secretary of housing and urban development, a friend implored him to turn down the job to preserve the reputation he had earned as a brilliant neurosurgeon and lost, in part, as a politician.

headline.main: Ben Carson of HUD on His Vexing Reign: Brain Surgery Was Easier Than This
headline.print_headline: Brain Surgery No Match for HUD, Carson Says
